## ğŸ“œ 11. Grammar Rules (Synergex Syntax Laws)

To ensure clarity and consistency, follow these **core grammar rules**:

1. **All expressions must begin and end with a system or kernel.**  
   âœ… `âŸ¦AâŸ§ â†’ âŸ¦BâŸ§`  
   âŒ `â†’ âŸ¦BâŸ§`

2. **Feedback loops must be closed:** `âˆ®( ... â†’ ... â†’ ... )`  
   âœ… `âˆ®(âŸ¦SensorâŸ§ â†’ âŸ¦ProcessorâŸ§ â†’ âŸ¦ActuatorâŸ§ â†’ âŸ¦SensorâŸ§)`

3. **Emergence (`âŠ—`) requires irreducibility.**  
   Use only when the result is *qualitatively new*.

4. **Isomorphism (`â‰£`) must be justified by shared `â—ˆ`-kernel(s).**  
   âœ… `âŸ¦AâŸ§ â‰£ âŸ¦BâŸ§ via â—ˆ_X`

5. **Recursive structures must be bounded.**  
   âœ… `âŸ¦SâŸ§ âŠ‚ âŸ¦Sâ‚Šâ‚âŸ§ âŠ‚ âŸ¦Sâ‚Šâ‚‚âŸ§`

6. **Open boundaries (`âˆ`) require at least one external interaction.**  
   âœ… `âŸ¦CellâˆâŸ§ â†’ âŸ¦EnvironmentâŸ§`

